      "writtenOn": "2020-03-26T19:02:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Not a fan of fire-and-forget. It may lead to weird states (like a ton of goroutines if DeleteArchiveTasks is slow). Considering the acking loop is already in a separate goroutine, is there harm in making sendIt block until it successfully deletes stuff?",
