        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-26T19:02:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If I read the docs correctly, one does not simply call Reset: https://golang.org/pkg/time/#Timer.Reset\n\n\u003e Reset should be invoked only on stopped or expired timers with drained channels. If a program has already received a value from t.C, the timer is known to have expired and the channel drained, so t.Reset can be used directly. If a program has not yet received a value from t.C, however, the timer must be stopped and—if Stop reports that the timer expired before being stopped—the channel explicitly drained\n\nMaybe not following this protocol is what causing bugs in the dispatcher?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 219,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 219,
        "endChar": 53
      },
